Assignment 2: Medium Level

Topic: Spring Boot REST API That Returns Java Bean as JSON

Description:
Create a Spring Boot REST API that manages a collection of books. Implement the following features:

Endpoint: /api/books

HTTP Method: GET

Response: Return a JSON array of book objects.
Example response:

css
Copy code
[    {        "id": 1,        "title": "Book 1",        "author": "Author 1"    },    {        "id": 2,        "title": "Book 2",        "author": "Author 2"    },    ...]
Implement CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for managing books.

POST /api/books: Create a new book.
GET /api/books/{id}: Retrieve a specific book by its ID.
PUT /api/books/{id}: Update an existing book.
DELETE /api/books/{id}: Delete a book by its ID.
